            <title>[DERBY-5467] Copyright notice in the API documentation (generated by the Javadoc tool) is outdated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5467</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ending year in the copyright notice used in the API documentation hasn&apos;t been updated. Currently the year 2007 or 2008 is being used.&lt;br/&gt;
Manually modifying the copyright notice is trivial, but has to be done once a year. It may be possible to automate this (i.e. use current year, or the year of the last change in the code repository?).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Out of curiosity, should the year be updated even if no changes have been made? (somewhat relevant if we decide to automate the update)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
