                            <comment id="13128857" author="rhillegas" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 14:21:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for catching this, Kristian. I think that the end year in the copyright notice should be changed to be the $&lt;/p&gt;
{copyright.year}
&lt;p&gt; variable. That variable is updated when the release manager builds a release candidate. IANAL but I don&apos;t think we will lose any legal protections if we automatically update the end year even when nothing visible has changed. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13128905" author="kristwaa" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 15:27:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for telling about the copyright.year property, Rick.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching patch 1a, which uses that property for the end year in the copyright notice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13128919" author="rhillegas" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 15:52:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Kristian. The patch looks good to me. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13131491" author="kristwaa" created="Thu, 20 Oct 2011 10:47:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed patch 1a to trunk with revision 1186691, and backported it to 10.8 with revision 1186697.&lt;br/&gt;
Closing the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
